{"author":{"id":"5e53c9bce7eeb69e347743575f6133426338c29498e200aa8bf1bef46209d02a"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1540475444,"nonce":"vQdXOco/tYT+BsJYELW4oFgVw1k=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQzMzA1ODg0Mg==","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/720#issuecomment-433058842"},"message":"I don't know, I am not aware of the history of `__dbkeys__` or what tools use it, and why they use it vs. `all_fasta`. However, since the data_manager_fetch_genome_dbkeys_all_fasta DM appears to be designed to update both tables, it seems reasonable that our older sequences that have lengths available should be added to `__dbkeys__`.\n\nFor pre-DM sequences, most (all) of these should already have lengths in `/cvmfs/data.galaxyproject.org/byhand/lengths`.\n\nFor sequences fetched with the non-`__dbkey__`-aware data_manager_fetch_genome_all_fasta, it looks like we'd need to generate lengths.\n\nDoes this sound correct? I can do the necessary table/location changes if so.","files":null},{"type":3,"timestamp":1540477411,"nonce":"wHBFxfjmV08PvEVtEq6/j6ZLhi4=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQzMzA3MTMzOQ==","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/720#issuecomment-433071339"},"message":"Turns out the UCSC update script already fetches [all the lengths](http://datacache.galaxyproject.org/managed/len/ucsc/). So these just need to be added to a location file and the `__dbkeys__` data table.","files":null},{"type":3,"timestamp":1540482637,"nonce":"lFH/SBymGJfrA/5zGtcQZ1Imu5Y=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQzMzEwNTAyMQ==","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/720#issuecomment-433105021"},"message":"Ok, all the UCSC builds are now in `__dbkeys__` on usegalaxy.org.","files":null}]}